view.name: Two Million LastFM User Profiles
view.description: Almost 2 million (1,840,647) user profiles extracted from the Last.fm API around Christmas, 2012.

columns.name: Registered Unix Timestamp
columns.description: When the user registered, in a Unix Timestamp format. The timezone is UTC.

columns.name: LastFM ID
columns.description:
The numeric user ID assigned by Last.fm.

It's pretty meaningless for us, but it may be useful to you.

columns.name: Shard
columns.description: This is a 2 character shard (the first 2 characters of a sha1 hash of the username, actually) I used for data management.
